    <body>
      <div type="mūlam" rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TNV14">
      <l>muntiya nūlōr moḻintaveṇ maṇattiluṅ</l>
<l>kantiruva muṟaimai kaḷaveṉap paṭumē.</l></lg>
<p xml:lang="en">Amongst the eight [types of] marriage mentioned by those prior theoreticians, the <hi rend="italic">kaniruvam</hi> custom is called <hi rend="italic">kaḷavu</hi></p>
</div>
</body>
</text>
<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition" corresp="#Ed">
    <body>
      <head xml:lang="en">Commentary</head>
      <p xml:id="TNV14comm1">e-tu. kaikōḷ iraṇṭiṉ uḷḷuṅ kaḷavoḻukkām āṟuṇarttutaṉutaliṟṟu.</p>
      <p xml:lang="en">The quoted [<hi rend="italic">cūttiram</hi>] intends to make known the way in which, 
      of the two [which form] <hi rend="italic">kaikōḷ</hi>, the <hi rend="italic">kaḷavu</hi> conduct occurs.</p>
      <p xml:id="TNV14comm2">toṉṉūl āciriyarkaḷāṟ collappaṭṭa vaṟanilai yoppu poruḷ kōṭeyvam arum poruḷ 
      vali nilai pēy nilai kantiruvam eṉappaṭṭa maṇam eṭṭiṉ uḷḷuṅ kantiruva vaḻakkam pōlvatu kaḷavoḻukkam ām eṉṟavāṟu.</p>
      <p xml:lang="en"><hi rend="italic">aṟanilai</hi>, <hi rend="italic">oppu</hi>, <hi rend="italic">poruḷ kōḷ</hi>, <hi rend="italic">teyvam</hi>, <hi rend="italic">arum poruḷ</hi>, <hi rend="italic">vali nilai</hi>, <hi rend="italic">pēy nilai</hi>, <hi rend="italic">kantiruvam</hi> which are 
      [all] mentioned by the teachers of the old treatises - amongst those eight [types of] marriage, the <hi rend="italic">kantiruvam</hi> 
      custom is the same as the <hi rend="italic">kaḷavu</hi> conduct.</p>
      